The University of Torontoâ€™s Dynamic Graphics Project is an interdisciplinary research laboratory within the Computer Science Department and the Computer Systems Research Institute. The labs mission is advanced research and graduate instruction; its theme is the enhancement of human creativity through advances in human-computer interaction, user interface design, and interactive computer graphics (Baecker, 1987). Our research spans input and interaction devices and techniques, user interface management systems, computersupported cooperative work, cognitive modelling, software engineering, computer program visualization, computer animation, multi-media, graphics modelling, and graphics rendering.